[size=4][u][b]Overview[/b][/u][/size]

Venworks - Dynamic Scenes Engine (DSE) is a Starfield creator framework for building reusable dynamic scenes inside POIs, caves, ships, space encounters, and man-made clutter pack-ins.

The short version: DSE gives mod authors a marker-and-manager system for preparing a location once, then letting scripts or DSE managers decide what appears there. A DSE-ready space can be repopulated, dressed, renamed, used for a quest scene, or turned into a local encounter without hand-building every variant as a separate location.

Players should mostly experience the result: more dynamic and replayable locations and encounters.

[size=3][b][u]Features[/u][/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Creator-built POIs that can spawn NPCs, chests, clutter, or scripted scene objects when the player enters, opens, reads, closes, or loads into the prepared area.[/*]
[*]Reusable encounter layouts using linked Scene A, Scene B, and Scene C marker groups for bosses, minions, and chests.[/*]
[*]Faction-based spawn groups for common Starfield encounter families such as Spacers, Ecliptic, Crimson Fleet, House Va'ruun, Syndicate, The First, Starborn, Sirens, Terrormorphs, biome predators, and robots.[/*]
[*]Clutter marker vocabulary for floor, surface, and outdoor placement points at practical authoring sizes.[/*]
[*]A shared foundation for future Venworks and compatible third-party dynamic encounter content.[/*]
[/list]

