[size=4][b][u]Usage Instructions[/u][/b][/size]

[size=3][b][u]For Players[/u][/b][/size]

Install this like a normal Starfield plugin requirement. DSE is mainly a framework, so it is most useful when another mod uses it or when you are looking at the included example content.

[list]
[*]Install Venworks - Core 2.1.1 or newer first.[/*]
[*]Install Venworks - Dynamic Scenes Engine after Venworks - Core.[/*]
[*]Keep DSE enabled before any mod that lists it as a requirement.[/*]
[*]If you are troubleshooting, enable DSE debug mode only when you need extra logging or authoring feedback.[/*]
[/list]

[size=3][b][u]For Mod Authors[/u][/b][/size]

The creator workflow is:

[list]
[*]Place the DSE manager or trigger object that owns the encounter.[/*]
[*]Place a center marker and map marker for the usable scene space.[/*]
[*]Place Scene A, Scene B, and/or Scene C markers for bosses, minions, and chests.[/*]
[*]Link every marker back to the manager with the matching DSE linked reference keyword.[/*]
[*]Configure spawn groups, faction data, chance conditions, and wave behavior values.[/*]
[*]Test a small encounter first, then expand to additional scene groups, waves, clutter, or DSE Manager behavior.[/*]
[/list]

Most setup problems come from marker links. If the manager fires but actors or chests do not appear, check that each marker is linked to the manager with the exact keyword used by the spawn group definition. Also remember each level (manager, faction selection, bosses/minions) has a randomization chance. Enabling debug mode will force all spawning to occur regardless of spawn chance.

[size=4][b][u]Requirements[/u][/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Starfield[/*]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/starfield/mods/7097]Venworks - Core[/url] 2.1.1 or newer[/*]
[/list]

[size=4][b][u]Compatibility[/u][/b][/size]

Currently we do not know of any compatibility issues

[size=4][u][b]Installation Instructions[/b][/u][/size]

[size=3][b][u]Via Vortex/MO2[/u][/b][/size]
Install as you normally would any Starfield mod. Make sure Venworks - Core 2.1.1 or newer is installed and enabled.

[size=3][b][u]Manually[/u][/b][/size]
Really, please use a mod manager :)

Download the current zip file. Place everything in the Data folder in the zip into the matching Data folder under your Starfield install directory, the same directory tree that contains Starfield.exe.

